## Overview

Over 5 years of professional experience in various technologies and roles in software development. Strong background in core CS and OO development. Interests include realtime networking. multiplayer game development platforms, cross platform mobile development, cloud network services, product evangelism and technical blogging.

## Experience

### [ShepHertz Technologies](http://www.shephertz.com)
**Technical Architect, July 2012 to present**

- Leading architecture and development of [AppWarp](http://www.appwarp.shephertz.com), realtime crossplatform cloud gaming networking platform.
- Design and implementation of AppWarp cloud services on top of Apache MINA Java framework for high performance socket servers.
- Designed the binary protocol for realtime communication over TCP and UDP.
- Design and development of multiple client SDKs (*Android, iOS, Unity, C++, Lua, ActionScript*)
- Contributed the HTML5 websocket encoder/decoder filter to Apache MINA community. 
- Driving product evangelism through [technical blogs](http://blogs.shephertz.com/author/dhruv), participation in forums and conferences.
- Actively participating in presales and providing technical support and trouble shooting help to customers.

### [Microsoft Corporation, Hyderabad, India](http://www.microsoft.com/en-in/msidc/default.aspx)

**Software Development Engineer II, July 2011 to July 2012**

- Development of client-side authentication infrastructure for [Microsoft Lync](http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/lync/) Web Meeting Client
- Development of REST based Instant Messaging feature in Android client.
- Worked in collaboration across different international teams and disciplines.

### [Microsoft Corporation, Redmond, USA](http://www.microsoft.com/)


**Software Development Engineer, March 2008 to June 2011**

- Developer in the [Microsoft Lync](http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/lync/) division, which is a SIP based communication and collaboration enterprise software solution.
- Worked on conferencing, audio and collaboration features for native (C++) Desktop Client, owning the communication between the client and different server components. 
- Worked with multiple teams across the group for two major releases of the desktop client.



